snippet.textDisplay:
All of the BTS members, TXT members, Lee Hyun looked so handsome, looked great. Lee Hyun (solo artist) appears @ 0:31. BTS - Jungkook: hair looks like 2 different shades of brown (lighter and really really dark), wearing black coat/jacket at beginning, J Hope: light - medium shade brown - ish hair, at beginning had on 2 chain (looks like 2 separate necklaces) necklaces. Jimin: light hair color, had on black suit jacket at beginning, V: really dark brown (or black) hair, appeared after Jungkook. Jin: black (or really dark brown) hair, wore white dress shirt at beginning, RM: gray/silver hair, Suga: Light hair color, had on black suit jacket, black & white striped shirt at beginning.I noticed that Jungkook was letting the tattoos on his hands show. I think ARMYs (BTS fans) won't truly know for sure if those tattoos are real unless Jungkook says something about them & that could never or it could be a very long time (same thing goes for Jimin's Nevermind tattoo).


TXT - Yeonjun: Wearing a striped suit jacket & glasses when RM greeted the TXT members somewhere within the first minute and a half of the video. Soobin: Black hair, wore glasses at beginning of video (came off a little bit later along with glasses), Beomgyu: Black hair, had black hat on at beginning of video. Taehyun: brown hair, wore striped suit jacket/black turtleneck at beginning. HueningKai: Has brown hair darker than Taehyun. At 1:37 he was wearing a bow tie as part of the outfit he had on at the time. Yeonjun imitated Bang Pdnim (founder, Co CEO is Lenzo Yoon) when he said "Ayo Hitman Bang introduces, Hit It, the second auditions".


When Jungkook said he was content with being small I thought that he isn't small. He is 5'10 which I think is a little taller than than or around the average height of a South Korean male (according to something I saw somewhere online). RM is 5'11 and Jin is 5'10 and a half (according the website kprofiles.com). Link: https://kprofiles.com/bts-bangtan-boys-members-profile/. I also liked the parts where it was people interviewing others (ex: there was 1 part where Lee Hyun interviewed Soobin, Jimin, Jin). When Jungkook was interviewing RM, V, Yeonjun, Beomgyu & asked about making a sub - unit RM said it would be himself, Suga, J Hope, Yeonjun & they would make a Cypher. I know that BTS rap line (RM, J Hope, Suga) made 4 Cyphers (Pt 1, 2, 3, 4). The first thing that popped into my head when RM said Yeonjun would be in the sub - unit is that I thought what he said was a little funny because V would want to be part of a Cypher if another one is ever made (I don't think another one will be made) & he is the biggest rap line fan boy. I think the suits gave the TXT members a little bit of an older, more mature vibe & the lighter/brighter colored outfits gave a more of a vibe that made them look young like they are, more of a fresh, innocent vibe/look. Somewhere in the last 2 to 3 mins of the video when Lee Hyun told the TXT members one piece of advice he has is to take care of their health even when they're swamped with work, I thought that was very good advice.
